sense.definition:
 (b. h.) 
to carry a load; 
to sustain; to endure.

an enclosed place, esp. 
the enclosure for cattle near a dwelling; 
stable.

 (סָטָה) 
faithless wife, a woman suspected of faithlessness, to whom the law, Num. V, 12-31, applies; 
Sotah.

